# Trivy IaC / vuln scan suppressions for Glad-Labs/poindexter.
#
# Each entry must include a rationale comment. CI policy: suppression
# without explanation is grounds for revert.
#
# DS-0002 ("Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile with non-root
# user") used to be suppressed for scripts/Dockerfile.voice-agent and
# scripts/Dockerfile.backup — both now run non-root after #488. The
# remaining 5 Dockerfiles (voice-bot, sdxl, wan, gpu-exporter,
# auto-embed) already had USER directives. No suppression is currently
# needed.
#
# Leave this file in place so the trivy-config CI step (which expects
# .trivyignore to exist) keeps working, and so future suppressions
# inherit the rationale-comment convention.
